.TH "wmi_rxon" 9 "wmi_rxon" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wmi_rxon \- turn radio on/off
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" wmi_rxon
.BI "(struct wil6210_priv *wil "  ","
.BI "bool on "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "wil" 12
driver data
.IP "on" 12
turn on if true, off otherwise
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only switch radio. Channel should be set separately.
No timeout for rxon - radio turned on forever unless some other call
turns it off
